calm%20down.%20Some%20calming%20treats%20your%20vet%20might%20recommend%20contain%20ingredients%20like%20L-theanine%2C%20magnolia%20and%20Phellodendron%20extracts%2C%20and%20thiamine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20do%20they%20work%3F%20%26quot%3BThere%20have%20been%20a%20few%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS1558787811000943%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escientific%20studies%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20suggest%20these%20products%20or%20their%20ingredients%20really%20can%20create%20a%20calming%20effect%20and%20reduce%20anxiety%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Brister.%20%26quot%3BFor%20instance%2C%20some%20dogs%20with%20thunderstorm%20anxiety%20improved%20on%20Solliquin.%20However%2C%20these%20products%20or%20their%20ingredients%20do%20not%20tend%20to%20alleviate%20stress%20or%20anxiety%20completely.%26quot%3B%20She%20adds%20that%20while%20some%20people%20report%20seeing%20significant%20improvement%20in%20their%20pet's%20anxiety%20using%20these%20products%2C%20many%20report%20no%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlways%20talk%20to%20your%20veterinarian%20if%20your%20pet%20exhibits%20signs%20of%20anxiety.%20They%20may%20recommend%20special%20behavioral%20approaches%20or%20medication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22358e3a6c-c0df-4bf0-9492-6b4f291ec922%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Best%20dental%20chews%5C%22%3EBest%20dental%20chews%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDental%20disease%20is%20a%20common%20health%20problem%20in%20dogs.%20It%20makes%20eating%20difficult%20and%20causes%20other%20symptoms%20like%20bad%20breath%2C%20excessive%20drooling%2C%20and%20significant%20oral%20pain.%20Regular%20at-home%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-toothpaste%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edental%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20yearly%20veterinary%20professional%20dental%20cleanings%20help%20prevent%20dental%20disease.%20Daily%20dental%20treats%20are%20also%20an%20easy%20way%20to%20help%20keep%20a%20dog's%20mouth%20clean%20and%20healthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20looking%20for%20a%20dental%20treat%2C%20it's%20best%20to%20stick%20with%20those%20approved%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.vohc.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVeterinary%20Oral%20Health%20Council%20(VOHC)%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIn%20much%20the%20same%20way%20that%20we%20have%20human%20dental%20products%20that%20have%20been%20approved%20by%20the%20American%20Dental%20Association%2C%20these%20products%20approved%20by%20the%20VOHC%20have%20demonstrated%20efficacy%20and%20are%20supported%20by%20studies%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Burns.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDental%20chews%2C%20however%2C%20don't%20come%20without%20risks%2C%20and%20they%20can%20be%20a%20choking%20hazard.%20To%20help%20prevent%20that%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.vohc.org%2Fchew.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVOHC%20recommends%3C%2Fa%3E%20buying%20dental%20chews%20appropriate%20for%20your%20dog's%20weight.%20Only%20give%20your%20dog%20a%20dental%20treat%20when%20you%20can%20supervise%20them%20%E2%80%94%20if%20a%20dog%20swallows%20dental%20treats%20rather%20than%20chewing%20them%2C%20we%20do%20not%20recommend%20giving%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b513b39e-3385-4d5d-8994-ba767d438e34%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Best%20for%20puppies%5C%22%3EBest%20for%20puppies%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20what%20treat%20you%20choose%20for%20your%20puppy%2C%20make%20sure%20it's%20small.%20Smaller-sized%20treats%20are%20an%20excellent%20option%20for%20reinforcing%20positive%20behaviors%20without%20overfeeding%2C%20says%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fantonio-demarco-b7a901116%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Antonio%20DeMarco%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20medical%20director%20and%20owner%20of%20GoodVets%20in%20Lee's%20Summit%2C%20Missouri.%20Treats%20formulated%20specifically%20for%20puppies%20and%20training%20treats%20are%20always%20good%20options.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20using%20the%20treats%20for%20training%2C%20make%20sure%20your%20puppy%20finds%20them%20tasty.%20You%20might%20have%20to%20experiment%20to%20find%20out%20what%20your%20dog%20loves%20best.%20Also%2C%20consider%20having%20a%20variety%20so%20your%20puppy%20doesn't%20get%20bored%20with%20their%20treats.%20Texture%20also%20matters.%20While%20soft%20is%20always%20best%2C%20DeMarco%20says%20you%20should%20be%20able%20to%20break%20a%20crunchy%20treat%20with%20your%20fingers%20easily%2C%20or%20else%20it%20could%20damage%20your%20puppy's%20teeth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2245b9f070-7552-4a0e-83c9-f91a6a7c706d%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Best%20for%20senior%20dogs%5C%22%3EBest%20for%20senior%20dogs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAging%20canines%20can%20face%20numerous%20health%20issues.%20Many%20senior%20dogs%20struggle%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vet.cornell.edu%2Fdepartments-centers-and-institutes%2Friney-canine-health-center%2Fcanine-health-information%2Fperiodontal-disease%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edental%20problems%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20choosing%20a%20soft-textured%20treat%20can%20be%20beneficial.%20Another%20consideration%20is%20the%20calorie%20content%20of%20treats%2C%20says%20Bullen.%20As%20many%20senior%20dogs%20become%20less%20active%2C%20they%20may%20gain%20weight%2C%20leading%20to%20conditions%20like%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fextension.okstate.edu%2Farticles%2F2022%2Fpet_health_obesity.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediabetes%20and%20cardiovascular%20disease%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20treats%20for%20senior%20dogs%20include%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vet.cornell.edu%2Fdepartments-centers-and-institutes%2Friney-canine-health-center%2Fcanine-health-information%2Fhow-joint-supplements-can-help-orthopedic-conditions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eingredients%20that%20may%20benefit%20aging%20canines%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Glucosamine%20is%20a%20common%20ingredient%20in%20the%20best%20dog%20treats%20for%20seniors%2C%20and%20many%20people%20give%20glucosamine%20supplements%20to%20dogs%20with%20arthritis.%20It's%20possible%20glucosamine%20can%20reduce%20some%20of%20their%20pain%20and%20help%20them%20move%20better%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.akc.org%2Fexpert-advice%2Fhealth%2Fglucosamine-dogs-arthritis-joint-pain%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Kennel%20Club%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOmega%20fatty%20acids%2C%20like%20those%20found%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-fish-oils-for-dogs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20fish%20oil%20for%20dogs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20help%20support%20skin%20and%20coat%20health%20and%20are%20included%20in%20all%20of%20our%20picks.%20An%20antioxidant-rich%20diet%20may%20also%20help%20lessen%20the%20effects%20of%20brain%20aging%20in%20dogs%2C%20according%20to%20a%20study%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F12392784%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENeurobiological%20Aging%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Take%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20cranberries%2C%20which%20contain%20plenty%20of%20antioxidants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c71b0dcf-5c63-44ed-88ba-e1ced225c4fd%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Best%20for%20small%20dogs%5C%22%3EBest%20for%20small%20dogs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESize%20is%20something%20to%20consider%20when%20selecting%20treats%20for%20small%20dogs.%20%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20consider%20what%20your%20pet%20can%20handle%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Burns.%20Treats%20for%20small%20dogs%20are%20often%20smaller%20than%20those%20for%20large%20dogs.%20Many%20manufacturers%20specify%20whether%20a%20treat%20is%20for%20a%20smaller%20dog%2C%20so%20when%20you%20read%20the%20packaging%2C%20check%20if%20the%20treat%20is%20appropriate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20some%20small%20dogs%20are%20perfectly%20fine%20eating%20a%20treat%20meant%20for%20a%20large%20dog%2C%20as%20long%20as%20it's%20not%20so%20big%20that%20it%20becomes%20a%20choking%20hazard.%20Also%2C%20pay%20attention%20to%20the%20calorie%20count.%20Calories%20from%20treats%20quickly%20add%20up%2C%20especially%20for%20small%20dogs%20whose%20calorie%20needs%20typically%20aren't%20as%20high%20as%20those%20for%20larger%20dogs.%20%26quot%3BThe%20'recommended'%20amount%20on%20the%20box%20%5Bof%20small%20dog%20treats%5D%20usually%20grossly%20overestimates%20their%20needs%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Bullen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2276db3dc9-5d80-4aa3-bb67-adf20cdf234d%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Best%20for%20large%20dogs%5C%22%3EBest%20for%20large%20dogs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20you%20might%20do%20with%20small%20dogs%2C%20you%20can%20check%20a%20treat's%20packaging%20to%20see%20if%20it's%20labeled%20for%20large%20dogs.%20However%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20skip%20over%20small%20treats.%20Burns%20says%20she%20has%20watched%20giant%20dogs%20slowly%20eat%20small%20treats.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20rare%2C%20some%20large%20dogs%20might%20vacuum%20small%20treats%20and%20aspirate%20them%20into%20their%20lungs%2C%20leading%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.merckvetmanual.com%2Fdog-owners%2Flung-and-airway-disorders-of-dogs%2Fpneumonia-in-dogs%23v3206670%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Easpiration%20pneumonia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20condition%20needing%20prompt%20veterinary%20treatment.%20If%20you're%20concerned%20that%20your%20pup%20will%20eat%20small-sized%20treats%20too%20quickly%2C%20err%20on%20the%20side%20of%20caution%20and%20choose%20a%20larger%20treat.%20Our%20recommendations%20are%20bigger%20in%20size%2C%20so%20it's%20less%20likely%20a%20dog%20will%20aspirate%20on%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a6beb360-3871-4bba-98e3-31bcec54470e%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20to%20look%20for%5C%22%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%20in%20dog%20treats%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EIngredient%20and%20calorie%20information%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIdeally%2C%20a%20treat's%20packaging%20should%20include%20the%20ingredients%20and%20calories%20per%20treat.%20If%20this%20information%20doesn't%20appear%20on%20the%20label%2C%20it%20should%20be%20easy%20to%20find%20on%20the%20brand's%20website.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFlavor%20and%20texture%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20best%20dog%20treats%20for%20your%20pup%20will%20include%20ingredients%20and%20flavors%20they.%20If%20you're%20not%20sure%20what%20they%20prefer%2C%20try%20a%20few%20different%20flavors.%20Pumpkin%2C%20banana%2C%20sweet%20potato%2C%20and%20meats%20like%20chicken%20are%20favorites%20among%20dogs.%20For%20pups%20with%20dental%20issues%2C%20soft%20treats%20are%20best.%20If%20your%20dog%20doesn't%20have%20problems%20with%20their%20teeth%20and%20likes%20a%20good%20crunch%2C%20biscuits%20are%20an%20excellent%20choice.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EToxic%20ingredients%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Check%20the%20ingredients%20on%20each%20treat's%20label%20to%20ensure%20it%20doesn't%20contain%20ingredients%20that%20are%20harmful%20to%20dogs%2C%20like%20garlic%20and%20onion%20powder.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EProduct%20recalls%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAvoid%20brands%20with%20frequent%20or%20serious%20recalls.%20Check%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Fsafety%2Frecalls-market-withdrawals-safety-alerts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFDA%20Recalls%2C%20Market%20Withdrawals%2C%20and%20Safety%20Alerts%20database%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20see%20a%20list%20of%20product%20recalls%20for%20pet%20treats.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EMisleading%20claims%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAny%20treat%20with%20claims%20that%20sounded%20too%20good%20to%20be%20true%20was%20rated%20more%20poorly%20in%20our%20evaluation.%20%26quot%3BI%20counsel%20clients%20to%20look%20at%20the%20claims%2C%20and%20if%20they're%20too%20good%20to%20be%20true%20%E2%80%94%20like%20curing%20a%20disease%20state%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20probably%20not%20the%20best%20choice%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Bullen.%20Meanwhile%2C%20terms%20like%20%26quot%3Bnatural%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Breal%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bholistic%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bpremium%26quot%3B%20are%20marketing%20buzzwords%20that%20do%20not%20speak%20to%20a%20treat's%20quality%20or%20nutritional%20value.%20We%20didn't%20exclude%20these%20treats%20from%20our%20recommendations%2C%20but%20such%20labels%20didn't%20influence%20our%20choices.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EVOHC%20acceptance%20for%20dental%20treats%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Look%20for%20dental%20treats%20that%20the%20VOHC%20approves.%20Studies%20back%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20these%20treats.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2204fcfbf9-8f13-4bf5-99e9-3a00c4190471%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20we%20selected%5C%22%3EHow%20we%20selected%20the%20best%20dog%20treats%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20select%20the%20best%20dog%20treats%20for%20this%20guide%2C%20we%20consulted%20four%20veterinarians%2C%20including%20one%20specializing%20in%20animal%20nutrition%2C%20and%20a%20veterinary%20technician%20specializing%20in%20nutrition.%20Although%20our%20experts%20did%20not%20recommend%20specific%20products%2C%20they%20helped%20us%20determine%20what%20makes%20a%20good%20dog%20treat%20and%20what%20to%20avoid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20considered%20treats%20we%20feed%20our%20dogs%20and%20options%20from%20popular%20brands.%20Ultimately%2C%20we%20made%20our%20selections%20based%20on%20the%20criteria%20outlined%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BWhat%20to%20look%20for%20in%20dog%20treats%26quot%3B%20section.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2247adb33f-b3fc-46aa-8a2d-dc742c626a53%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22FAQs%5C%22%3EDog%20treats%20FAQs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%20data-test%3D%5C%22faq-question-field%5C%22%3EIs%20it%20okay%20to%20give%20my%20dog%20treats%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYes.%20%26quot%3BGiving%20your%20dog%20treats%20is%20a%20way%20of%20showing%20love%20and%20strengthening%20the%20human-animal%20bond%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Burns.%20However%2C%20she%20adds%20that%20too%20many%20treats%20can%20exceed%20a%20dog's%20recommended%20calorie%20intake.%20Limit%20how%20many%20treats%20you%20give%20your%20dog%20to%20avoid%20overfeeding.%20Your%20veterinarian%20can%20help%20you%20determine%20the%20appropriate%20calories%20to%20feed%20your%20dog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-test%3D%5C%22faq-question-field%5C%22%3EWhat%20is%20the%20best%20treat%20to%20give%20a%20dog%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20good%20for%20one%20dog%20isn't%20necessarily%20suitable%20for%20another.%20Fortunately%2C%20some%20of%20the%20best%20dog%20treats%20to%20give%20your%20pup%20in%20terms%20of%20convenience%2C%20health%2C%20and%20calories%20are%20probably%20already%20in%20your%20refrigerator%20or%20pantry.%20They%20include%20popular%20human%20food%20like%20peanut%20butter%20(without%20xylitol%2C%20which%20can%20be%20fatal%20to%20dogs)%2C%20apples%2C%20bananas%2C%20strawberries%2C%20plain%20air-popped%20popcorn%2C%20apples%2C%20carrots%2C%20celery%2C%20and%20green%20beans%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aspca.org%2Fnews%2Fsharing-caring-foods-you-can-safely-share-your-pet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Society%20for%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Cruelty%20to%20Animals%3C%2Fa%3E%20(ASPCA).%20Make%20sure%20to%20remove%20all%20seeds%20and%20feed%20appropriate-sized%20pieces%20to%20your%20dog.%20The%20treats%20that%20we%20selected%20can%20serve%20as%20a%20guide%20for%20you%20to%20choose%20treats%20for%20your%20dog.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-test%3D%5C%22faq-question-field%5C%22%3EHow%20many%20treats%20can%20I%20give%20my%20dog%20in%20a%20day%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTreats%20shouldn't%20make%20up%20more%20than%2010%25%20of%20your%20dog's%20total%20daily%20calories%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Bullen.%20Because%20that%20can%20be%20tough%20to%20determine%2C%20Bullen%20broke%20down%20the%20maximum%20amount%20of%20daily%20%26quot%3Btreat%26quot%3B%20calories%20that%20dogs%20can%20have%20according%20to%20body%20weight.%20Remember%20that%20treats%20are%20a%20tasty%20bonus%20to%20your%20dog's%20regular%20food%2C%20so%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20give%20your%20dog%20this%20amount%20every%20day.%20Also%2C%20your%20dog's%20health%20status%20and%20lifestyle%20affect%20daily%20caloric%20needs%20and%20whether%20they%20should%20have%20any%20treats%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E10-pound%20dog%3A%20No%20more%20than%2020%20to%2025%20calories%20in%20treats%2Fday%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E25-pound%20dog%3A%20No%20more%20than%2050%20calories%20in%20treats%2Fday%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E50-pound%20dog%3A%20No%20more%20than%2080%20calories%20in%20treats%2Fday%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E75-pound%20dog%3A%20No%20more%20than%20100%20calories%20in%20treats%2Fday%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E100-pound%20dog%3A%20No%20more%20than%20125%20calories%20in%20treats%2Fday%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch3%20data-test%3D%5C%22faq-question-field%5C%22%3EWhat%20happens%20if%20I%20give%20my%20dog%20too%20many%20treats%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EToo%20many%20treats%20lead%20to%20too%20many%20calories%2C%20which%20can%20lead%20to%20your%20dog%20becoming%20overweight%2C%20Burns%20says.%20A%202018%20report%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpetobesityprevention.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAssociation%20for%20Pet%20Obesity%20Prevention%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%2056%25%20of%20dogs%20in%20the%20United%20States%20were%20either%20overweight%20or%20obese.%20That%20excess%20weight%20can%20have%20many%20negative%20health%20consequences%2C%20including%20diabetes%2C%20arthritis%2C%20cancer%2C%20and%20high%20blood%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-test%3D%5C%22faq-question-field%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhich%20dog%20treats%20do%20vets%20recommend%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EBullen%20provides%20a%20few%20tips%20when%20talking%20with%20dog%20owners%20about%20what%20treats%20are%20suitable%20for%20their%20dogs.%20First%2C%20evaluate%20any%20claims%20on%20the%20packages.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20claims%20are%20too%20good%20to%20be%20true%2C%20the%20treat%20probably%20isn't%20a%20good%20idea%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20She%20also%20recommends%20looking%20for%20treats%20with%20an%20ingredient%20list%20and%20calorie%20information%20on%20the%20package.%20If%20you%20can't%20find%20that%20information%20on%20the%20package%2C%20look%20for%20it%20on%20the%20manufacturer's%20website.%20Read%20the%20label%20to%20ensure%20the%20treat%20does%20not%20contain%20ingredients%20that%20are%20toxic%20to%20dogs.%20Bullen%20has%20seen%20treats%20with%20garlic%20and%20onion%20powder%2C%20both%20well-known%20toxins%20to%20dogs.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EKeep%20in%20mind%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aafco.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAssociation%20of%20American%20Feed%20Control%20Officials%3C%2Fa%3E%20(AAFCO)%20regulates%20the%20sale%20and%20distribution%20of%20pet%20food%2C%20but%20treats%20aren't%20included.%20Because%20treats%20aren't%20intended%20to%20be%20nutritionally%20balanced%2C%20they%20don't%20need%20to%20meet%20the%20same%20nutritional%20requirements%20described%20in%20our%20guide%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-food%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20dog%20food%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftalkspetfood.aafco.org%2Ftreatsandchews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAAFCO%20says%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20word%20%26quot%3Btreat%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bsnack%26quot%3B%20must%20appear%20on%20the%20packaging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-test%3D%5C%22faq-question-field%5C%22%3EHow%20should%20I%20introduce%20a%20new%20treat%20to%20my%20dog%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20give%20your%20dog%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20the%20treat.%20Bullen%20says%20to%20monitor%20your%20dog%20to%20ensure%20they%20can%20tolerate%20the%20treat%20and%20don't%20show%20any%20signs%20of%20sensitivity%20like%20vomiting%2C%20diarrhea%2C%20itching%2C%20and%20scratching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-treats%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1765405825000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6939f08a7ecd1d1da6635410%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-treats%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22We%20asked%20vets%20how%20to%20choose%20the%20best%20dog%20treats.%20Our%20top-rated%20picks%20include%20treats%20for%20puppies%20and%20small%20dogs%2C%20training%2C%20calming%2C%20and%20dental%20care.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Karen%20Asp%2CKarie%20Johnson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-treats%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rick%20Riordan%20and%20%E2%80%98Percy%20Jackson%E2%80%99%20EPs%20Unpack%20How%20Season%202%20Changes%20%E2%80%98The%20Sea%20of%20Monsters%E2%80%99%20Book%3A%20%E2%80%98As%20the%20Kids%20Say%2C%20It%20Hits%20Different%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1765405800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F12%2F173997_1061_90f8e0ba.jpeg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236604563%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22SPOILER%20ALERT%3A%20This%20story%20contains%20spoilers%20for%20the%20first%20two%20episodes%20of%20%E2%80%9CPercy%20Jackson%20and%20the%20Olympians%E2%80%9D%20Season%202.%20The%20%E2%80%9CPercy%20Jackson%E2%80%9D%20fandom%